.TH PYELFTOOLS 1 "2026-05-06" "InterGenOS" "InterGenOS Manual"
.SH NAME
pyelftools \- pure-Python ELF and DWARF parser library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python3 -c "import elftools"
.PP
This is a Python library, not a command-line tool. The PyPI distribution
ships small example scripts (\fIelf_show_*.py\fR, \fIdwarf_*.py\fR) but
the primary use is as a build-time dependency in other packages.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pyelftools
is a pure-Python library for parsing ELF and DWARF binary formats. It
exposes the
.B elftools
Python module.

.SS Why InterGenOS ships it
systemd 259 uses
.B pyelftools
at meson configure-time to generate
.IR linuxx64.efi.stub ,
the systemd-stub PE binary that
.IR scripts/build-uki.sh
wraps the kernel + initramfs + cmdline into for the Unified Kernel
Image (UKI). Without
.B pyelftools
present in the build environment, systemd's meson option
.IR bootloader=auto
silently resolves to disabled, the stub never gets built, and the UKI
build fails much later with an opaque "STUB not found" error.

Shipping pyelftools as a core-tier package closes that silent-failure
path. systemd's recipe should declare
.B pyelftools
in its host-deps so the dependency is explicit at recipe level.
